{
  "message": "fuzz(ext4-fast-commit): 19 structured seeds across every FcTag\n\nfuzz_ext4_fast_commit drives ffs_journal::replay_fast_commit through\nJBD2 fast-commit tag streams. Each tag is a u16 type + u16 length +\npayload, with valid types Link / Unlink / AddRange / DelRange / Creat\n/ Inode / Pad / Tail / Head. The replay loop tracks Head\u2192Tail\ntransactions and sets `fallback_required` on any error path.\n\nExisting 4 ad-hoc seeds (byte, empty, clean_replay, missing_tail)\ncovered only the simplest happy and missing-tail cases. New 19 seeds\ntarget every documented branch:\n\n  Happy paths (one tag per type):\n  * HEAD + PAD + TAIL\n  * HEAD + Creat + TAIL\n  * HEAD + Link + TAIL\n  * HEAD + Unlink + TAIL\n  * HEAD + AddRange + TAIL  (16-byte payload: ino, logical, length,\n    physical)\n  * HEAD + DelRange + TAIL  (12-byte payload)\n  * HEAD + Inode + TAIL\n  * HEAD + (Creat + AddRange + Inode) + TAIL \u2014 multi-op transaction\n  * Two clean transactions back-to-back\n\n  Error paths the parser must surface as fallback_required:\n  * Unknown tag type (0xBADF) inside a transaction\n  * Tail without preceding Head\n  * Operation without preceding Head\n  * Truncated tag \u2014 declared length exceeds remaining bytes\n  * HEAD with payload < 16 bytes\n  * HEAD + TAIL with TAIL payload < 8 bytes\n  * Trailing non-zero bytes after a clean transaction (post-loop\n    sentinel check)\n\n  Termination shapes:\n  * Explicit `\\x00\\x00\\x00\\x00` zero-terminator (early-break path)\n  * Clean transaction followed by zero-terminator\n  * 400-byte PAD payload inside a valid transaction (no-op, must\n    not advance state)\n\nValidated by an 11 s libFuzzer run: 1.6 M executions over the new\ncorpus, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
